  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] cousins, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Solomon Schleime Schuster and his brother Elichaim and his brother Maishe, all three of them were hiding in the same area where we were hiding.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on several occasions I met with the youngest of-- Maishe He's the guy who's still alive in Mexico City, owns a travel agency there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He would go out begging for food or we would arrange to meet at a certain place in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, he knew where we hiding at Dekar's.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he never told us where they were hiding.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the reason was that he said, look, what you don't know, you cannot give away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If you are captured by the Germans, they will torture you until you give us away, so if you don't know where we are, you can't tell them where we are.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he never told us where they were hiding, even though we were a very short distance from each other, neighbors practically.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One day a farmer and his wife came by.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we could never tell.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think they were chopping wood or picking berries or whatever.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But once they saw us and saw the bunker open, we felt that we could no longer use that, because chances were good that they were going to tell someone.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know what I did not describe yet, and that is not really my own personal story, but related to my family and in a way related to me, my cousins Schleime and Elichaim and Maishe survived and managed to get to the forest even though they were-- they went into town to be deported during the liquidation.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And what had happened there is that they were all gathered into town.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
